		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>flash programming with socketted bios</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Hello... I'm interested in programming flash roms / eproms / eeproms using an old PC motherboard with a socketted BIOS... There's some software out there that allows for this, but I'm reluctant to potentially overwrite the PCs BIOS in the process...
<br />
<br />I was wondering: Has anyone tried this? How do you get the PC to run without its BIOS while you flash the chip? Also, which type of chip (eprom, eeprom, flash rom) should be used in this case?
<br />
<br />Thanks.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
