		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I heard you have to activate BIOS shadowing, so that your PC can use a copy of the BIOS ROM instead, allowing you to remove the chip while the PC is running and replace it with the chip to be programmed. Sounds very tricky, though!
<br />
<br />And yeah, you'd have to use the exact same kind of chip that's already there, so you'll have to check what it is.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


